<root>
    <pg ref="">
        <title>INTRODUCTION</title>
        <lg>
            <l n="1">The parents of the learned child</l>
            <l n="2">(His father and his mother)</l>
            <l n="3">Were utterly aghast to note</l>
            <l n="4">The facts he would at random quote</l>
            <l n="5">On creatures curious, rare and wild;</l>
            <l n="6">And wondering, asked each other:</l>
        </lg>
        <pgNum n="206">[206]</pgNum>
    </pg>
    <pg ref="">
        <fig>
            <img alt="An idle child"
                src="https://github.com/JiayuanWen/Belloc-More-Beasts/blob/main/pics/manreading.png"
            />
        </fig>
        <lg>
            <l n="1">"An idle little child like this,</l>
            <l n="2">How is it that he knows</l>
            <l n="3">What years of close analysis</l>
            <l n="4">Are powerless to disclose?</l>
        </lg>
        <lg>
            <l n="1">Our brains are trained, our books are big,</l>
            <l n="2">And yet we always fail</l>
        </lg>
        <pgNum n="207">[207]</pgNum>
    </pg>
    <pg ref="">
        <fig>
            <img alt="The lion"
                src="https://github.com/JiayuanWen/Belloc-More-Beasts/blob/main/pics/lionsreading.png"
            />
        </fig>
        <lg>
            <l n="1">To answer why the Guinea-pig</l>
            <l n="2">Is born without a tail.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg>
            <l n="1">Or why the Wanderoo<noteref letter="A">[A]</noteref> should rant</l>
            <l n="2">In wild, unmeaning rhymes,</l>
        </lg>
        <pgNum n="208">[208]</pgNum>
    </pg>
    <pg ref="">
        <fig>
            <img alt="Indian elephant reading The Times"
                src="https://github.com/JiayuanWen/Belloc-More-Beasts/blob/main/pics/elephantreading.png"
            />
        </fig>
        <lg>
            <l n="1">Whereas the Indian Elephant</l>
            <l n="2">Will only read The Times.</l>
        </lg>
        <pgNum n="209">[209]</pgNum>
    </pg>
    <pg ref="">
        <fig>
            <img alt="Interviewed the Pelican"
                src="https://github.com/JiayuanWen/Belloc-More-Beasts/blob/main/pics/pelican.png"/>
        </fig>
        <lg>
            <l n="1">Perhaps he found a way to slip</l>
            <l n="2">Unnoticed to the Zoo,</l>
            <l n="3">And gave the Pachyderm a tip,</l>
            <l n="4">Or pumped the Wanderoo.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg>
            <l n="1">Or even by an artful plan</l>
            <l n="2">Deceived our watchful eyes,</l>
            <l n="3">And interviewed the Pelican,</l>
            <l n="4">Who is extremely wise."</l>
        </lg>
        <pgNum n="210">[210]</pgNum>
    </pg>
    <pg ref="">
        <fig>
            <img alt="This little book" src=""/>
        </fig>
        <lg>
            <l n="1">"Oh! no," said he, in humble tone,</l>
            <l n="2">With shy but conscious look,</l>
            <l n="3">"Such facts I never could have known</l>
            <l n="4">But for this little book."</l>
        </lg>
        <pgNum n="211">[211]</pgNum>
    </pg>
    <foot>FOOTNOTE: <def><noteref letter="A">[A]</noteref> Sometimes called the "Lion-tailed or
            tufted Baboon of Ceylon."</def></foot>
</root>
